-- Shares of Buffett-backed BYD fall 5 pct after $551 mln share sale plan
-- By Donny Kwok
-- Sun May 25, 2014 09:44PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, May 26 (Reuters) - Shares of Chinese carmaker BYD Co Ltd <1211.HK><002594.SZ> fell 5 percent in Hong Kong early on Monday after the company backed by investor Warren Buffett launched a new share issue seeking to raise up to $550 million.

In early trading the stock was changing hands at HK$39.10, while the benchmark Hang Seng Index <.HSI> was 0.4 percent higher. BYD said on Friday it would place 121.9 million new H-shares at HK$35 apiece, raising up to HK$4.27 billion ($551 million) for general working capital and fund business development.